Jenna Etheridge, News24 Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cape Town &ndash; A queue marshal was shot dead at a minibus taxi rank in central Johannesburg on Friday morning, Gauteng police said.The man, 37, had been busy at the back of the taxis when an unidentified man approached him, said Captain Kay Makhubela.He shot the marshal six times in the upper body at close range.The shooter was on the run. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.